4/Top_of_the_Rockies_-_Steep_Green_Canyons_in_the_Colorado_Rockies_-_NARA_-_7722426.jpg/1280px-Top_of_the_Rockies_-_Steep_Green_Canyons_in_the_Colorado_Rockies_-_NARA_-_7722426.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d4/Top_of_the_Rockies_-_Steep_Green_Canyons_in_the_Colorado_Rockies_-_NARA_-_7722426.jpg","cap":"Steep Green Canyons in the Colorado Rockies","desc":"Bright white clouds cast shadows over a valley filled with lush greenery in the Colorado Rockies along US Highway 24. Location: Colorado (39.127° N 106.743° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Jenette Purdy","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Top_of_the_Rockies_-_Steep_Green_Canyons_in_the_Colorado_Rockies_-_NARA_-_7722426.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Top_of_the_Rockies_-_The_Narrows_-_NARA_-_7722456.jpg/1280px-Top_of_the_Rockies_-_The_Narrows_-_NARA_-_7722456.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/37/Top_of_the_Rockies_-_The_Narrows_-_NARA_-_7722456.jpg","cap":"The Narrows","desc":"Winding through the Narrows, Highway 82 clings to the cliff as low lying clouds allow a glimpse at a peak near the Independence Pass ridgeline and the vibrant blue Colorado sky. Location: Colorado (39.139° N 106.767° W) Status: Public domain.","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Top_of_the_Rockies_-_The_Narrows_-_NARA_-_7722456.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/Top_of_the_Rockies_-_The_Summit_of_Independence_Pass_-_NARA_-_7722454.jpg/1280px-Top_of_the_Rockies_-_The_Summit_of_Independence_Pass_-_NARA_-_7722454.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d3/Top_of_the_Rockies_-_The_Summit_of_Independence_Pass_-_NARA_-_7722454.jpg","cap":"The Summit of Independence Pass","desc":"In this panoramic view, Highway 82 crosses the summit of Independence Pass at an elevation of 12,095 feet, one of the highest paved roads in the US. Stretching off to the west from the summit is the Roaring Fork River valley leading to Aspen, and to the east, the South Fork of Lake Creek leading to Twin Lakes and beyond. Location: Colorado (39.109° N 106.572° W) Status: Public domain.","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Top_of_the_Rockies_-_The_Summit_of_Independence_Pass_-_NARA_-_7722454.jpg"}]}